SIMPLE: blowtube
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blowtube
<hw>Blow"tube`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
blowgun.</def> <rj><au>Tylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A similar instrument, commonly of tin, used by boys
for discharging paper wads and other light missiles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Glassmaking)</fld> <def>A long wrought iron tube,
on the end of which the workman gathers a quantity of
⟦ldquo⟧metal⟦rdquo⟧ (melted glass), and through which he blows to expand
or shape it; -- called also <altname>blowing tube</altname>, and
<altname>blowpipe</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blow valve</ent>⟦br⟧
